00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:21.630
That's impossible.

00:09:23.750 --> 00:09:26.290
What about your parents?
Are they working at this hour?

00:09:26.290 --> 00:09:28.210
Mom's probably at work,

00:09:28.210 --> 00:09:29.920
and Dad hasn't lived here since the divorce.

00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:31.130
So don't worry.

00:09:32.330 --> 00:09:33.710
Then that means...

00:09:34.880 --> 00:09:37.750
"Hey, my mom's out tonight."

00:09:38.420 --> 00:09:39.630
"Wanna come over?"

00:09:39.750 --> 00:09:40.960
The classic situation!

00:09:40.960 --> 00:09:42.960
But you're the one who said you wanted to come over.

00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:49.130
<i>This is the first time I've had a girl in my room
since I started middle school.</i>

00:09:49.580 --> 00:09:51.790
<i>And she just has to sit on the bed.</i>

00:09:51.790 --> 00:09:53.000
<i>Why there?!</i>

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.630
What about the space between the wall and the bed?!

00:09:54.630 --> 00:09:55.630
No!

00:09:56.210 --> 00:09:57.670
<i>And now she's lying down...</i>

00:09:57.880 --> 00:10:00.790
Hey, this bed smells like you, Ko-kun!

00:10:00.790 --> 00:10:02.210
That's kind of raunchy!

00:10:02.210 --> 00:10:03.460
<i>And she's sleazy.</i>

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.210
Oh, there's a used tissue.

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:07.540
I blew my nose with that, obviously!

00:10:09.540 --> 00:10:11.670
<i>This is so unnerving!</i>

00:10:11.750 --> 00:10:12.960
Up we get...

00:10:13.540 --> 00:10:14.540
Anyway...

00:10:15.080 --> 00:10:16.880
Have you reconsidered, after all?

00:10:18.750 --> 00:10:19.750
What do you...

00:10:19.750 --> 00:10:21.580
You met with your friend, didn't you?

00:10:22.040 --> 00:10:24.210
I don't have to suck your blood to tell.

00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:26.710
You're unsure, Ko-kun.

00:10:27.420 --> 00:10:30.000
The vampire who never sucked blood...

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.250
Your friends...

00:10:31.250 --> 00:10:33.420
A detective who can kill vampires...

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:36.170
It'd be weird if you weren't unsure.

00:10:37.210 --> 00:10:39.830
Actually, a normal person wouldn't be unsure.

00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:42.630
He'd give up becoming a vampire
in favor of his friends.

00:10:45.250 --> 00:10:47.580
He asked me why I wanted to be one.

00:10:48.130 --> 00:10:49.710
Why become a vampire?

00:10:50.130 --> 00:10:51.130
And?

00:10:51.960 --> 00:10:55.170
I thought about it, but it's because I like the night.

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:57.000
The night's free.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:00.750
It's like a whole different world,
and people can be different there, too.

00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:02.460
That's why I like it.

00:11:03.250 --> 00:11:07.250
But lately, I've started seeing that it's not all just fun.

00:11:07.880 --> 00:11:09.170
I was okay with that, though.

00:11:09.630 --> 00:11:12.960
Because you acknowledge all of my emotions.

00:11:13.830 --> 00:11:16.330
But it's different if there's actual harm.

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:20.540
It's one thing if it's just me,
but if I were to hurt my friends...

00:11:21.670 --> 00:11:25.170
And when I think about it,
I have plenty of fun as it is right now!

00:11:25.170 --> 00:11:30.290
I mean, it's not like you're that eager to
make me your offspring, anyway!

00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:34.130
Even if I don't become a vampire...

00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:37.830
Yeah...

00:11:44.670 --> 00:11:47.130
Let me help you with your decision.

00:11:47.210 --> 00:11:48.460
Listen up.

00:11:48.830 --> 00:11:52.130
Why do you think the night felt so fun to you?

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:54.830
Because there's freedom?

00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:56.790
Yeah, that's definitely true.

00:11:57.170 --> 00:12:02.500
But taking that further,
it's because it's out of the ordinary.

00:12:03.170 --> 00:12:05.630
Your ordinary is daytime and school.

00:12:05.630 --> 00:12:07.290
Nighttime is the opposite.

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:09.330
I'm sure it was exhilarating.

00:12:09.790 --> 00:12:11.380
But think about it.

00:12:11.790 --> 00:12:15.170
Right now, do you get equally
as exhilarated or more

00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:17.960
compared to that first night you went out?

00:12:18.580 --> 00:12:22.710
Isn't the fun you feel part of the ordinary now?

00:12:25.460 --> 00:12:31.130
Ko-kun, anything out of the ordinary
never lasts for long, you know.

00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:35.460
Being a vampire's just boring.

00:12:36.580 --> 00:12:39.170
I'm sorry I lied to you.

00:12:40.380 --> 00:12:43.330
It's been decades since I became a vampire,

00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:45.130
but I've never been anything but bored.

00:12:45.670 --> 00:12:49.420
I just wait for time to pass as I spend
each shallow, meaningless day.

00:12:50.630 --> 00:12:53.580
Well, thanks to that I'm a boss at
video games now, though!

00:12:55.080 --> 00:12:56.080
Why?

00:12:56.670 --> 00:12:59.580
Why did you try to show me just the fun stuff?

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:01.960
Why did I?

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:05.580
Maybe because that's how I wanted to be.

00:13:08.210 --> 00:13:09.420
I see...

00:13:10.380 --> 00:13:12.250
Anyway, I'm gonna head home for now.

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:14.710
Huh? H-hold on! I still-

00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:30.330
What?

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:32.460
S-sorry! I didn't mean-

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:39.790
Thought I was gonna kiss you?

00:13:39.790 --> 00:13:41.380
<i>You weren't?!</i>

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:55.920
<b>12th Night: My Mom’s Out Tonight</b>

00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:04.630
<b>Private Detective</b>

00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:04.630
<b>ANKO UGUISU</b>

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.630
Hey, Yamori-kun.

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:09.670
I thought it was about time you called.

00:14:10.710 --> 00:14:11.960
"Can you spare some time, miss?"

00:14:11.960 --> 00:14:16.170
"Why don't we go to a cafe or something and
slip into a scandalous relationship?"

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:21.830
Wait, that's not it?

00:14:21.830 --> 00:14:23.670
Why did you think it was?

00:14:23.790 --> 00:14:26.790
Jeez, I totally had that wrong!

00:14:26.790 --> 00:14:28.250
Now that's embarrassing.

00:14:28.250 --> 00:14:29.630
You were serious?!

00:14:29.630 --> 00:14:31.170
Of course I was serious!

00:14:31.460 --> 00:14:34.630
I told you to hit on me properly next time, remember?!

00:14:34.630 --> 00:14:36.580
Why are you kind of angry?

00:14:36.580 --> 00:14:40.000
I like the idea of stringing
a middle schooler along for a change.

00:14:40.540 --> 00:14:44.330
I don't think it's such a bad deal for you, Yamori-kun.

00:14:45.210 --> 00:14:46.460
Where are you going?

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:50.630
You want to talk about vampires, no?

00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:53.250
Um...

00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:56.130
How much do you know about me, Miss Detective?

00:14:56.580 --> 00:15:01.420
You mean your idiotic
"Ooh, I wanna be a vampire dream"?

00:15:02.630 --> 00:15:04.750
Other than that, let's see...

00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:09.380
Your name is Ko Yamori, fourteen years old.
Single-mother household.

00:15:09.380 --> 00:15:12.710
You don't go to school but your grades
are reasonably good.

00:15:12.710 --> 00:15:17.790
You don't have a lot of hobbies but you like sneakers
and collect them secondhand for cheap.

00:15:17.790 --> 00:15:22.210
You have no experience with romance,
but you like girls with big boobs.

00:15:22.210 --> 00:15:27.130
You don't own porn but you sometimes save
those kinds of images on your phone,

00:15:27.130 --> 00:15:31.330
then delete them out of embarrassment later,
only to regret it and do it all over again.

00:15:31.330 --> 00:15:32.920
Huh?! Uh, what?! That's freaky!

00:15:32.920 --> 00:15:33.540
The first time you eja-

00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:34.750
That amount of detail is freaky!
The first time you eja-<b></b>

00:15:34.790 --> 00:15:36.000
What? How?!

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.380
Just joking!
Ha ha, gotcha!

00:15:38.380 --> 00:15:40.830
It's all speculation!
Deductive reasoning!

00:15:40.830 --> 00:15:42.250
Because I'm a detective, remember?

00:15:42.380 --> 00:15:44.880
<i>How much of what she says is true?</i>

00:15:48.710 --> 00:15:52.130
Um, about wanting to be a vampire...

00:15:52.830 --> 00:15:56.040
Why are you against it, Miss Detective?

00:15:56.330 --> 00:15:57.880
That's a weird question to ask.

00:15:58.630 --> 00:16:01.960
Because vampires are evil from the
human perspective, of course.

00:16:04.210 --> 00:16:08.920
See, I think humans causing misfortune for
other humans is inevitable sometimes,

00:16:08.920 --> 00:16:11.000
depending on the time and situation,

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:14.500
but I think it's unacceptable for a vampire to cause it.

00:16:15.290 --> 00:16:19.040
People live among other humans.
You can't avoid conflict.

00:16:19.040 --> 00:16:23.130
But I can't allow misfortune that
never should have existed,

00:16:23.130 --> 00:16:25.290
intended by something that isn't human.

00:16:25.290 --> 00:16:27.670
Vampires only ever make people unhappy.

00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:30.500
You saw an example of that too.

00:16:30.880 --> 00:16:34.290
But you said that was only because
he didn't drink blood for ten years!

00:16:34.290 --> 00:16:35.500
That's right.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:39.710
Because he was a honorary human, who maintained
his pride as a human being to the very end.

00:16:41.170 --> 00:16:42.750
Can you say for sure?

00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:47.880
That when you become a vampire,
you'll be okay with drinking human blood?

00:16:47.880 --> 00:16:52.670
Or else never drink any and
live with the pain for ten long years?

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:05.040
Besides, considering you haven't fallen in love yet
despite the amount of contact you've had,

00:17:05.040 --> 00:17:08.250
I honestly doubt you'll ever get to be a vampire.

00:17:08.250 --> 00:17:08.880
That's not-

00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:10.580
Have you ever considered...
That's not-<b></b>

00:17:10.580 --> 00:17:15.000
that you might lack romantic urges to begin with?

00:17:17.580 --> 00:17:20.420
That would be a problem, wouldn't it?

00:17:20.420 --> 00:17:24.130
You definitely wouldn't get to be a vampire, 100%.

00:17:24.420 --> 00:17:26.750
But that's good, actually!

00:17:27.290 --> 00:17:31.380
There's no need for me to convince you otherwise now.

00:17:31.790 --> 00:17:33.250
But wait...

00:17:33.540 --> 00:17:35.750
Now there's a problem, isn't there?

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:38.960
You know about their existence,

00:17:38.960 --> 00:17:42.330
which means you're a liability for the vampires.

00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:45.540
Simultaneously, the vampire
who invited along an anomaly like you...

00:17:45.540 --> 00:17:47.580
Nazuna Nanakusa, was it?

00:17:47.580 --> 00:17:50.670
I don't think she'll be safe, either.

00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:54.080
They might just murder the both of you, you know?

00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:55.710
I-I don't want that!

00:17:55.710 --> 00:17:57.420
Then make your decision now.

00:17:58.040 --> 00:18:02.540
You can live as a human,
or become a vampire and get killed by me.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:04.080
Decide right now.

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:08.420
Do you really have the ability to kill vampires?

00:18:08.420 --> 00:18:09.880
You saw, didn't you?

00:18:09.880 --> 00:18:13.210
I can't tell you how,
but your fate depends on your answer.

00:18:15.880 --> 00:18:19.880
If it means you'll choose the proper life as a human,

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:21.880
I'll do anything.

00:18:22.130 --> 00:18:24.170
I'm prepared to do that.

00:18:24.500 --> 00:18:27.790
